remarks.para:
A typical transaction should use the following idiom:
	
		ISession sess = factory.OpenSession();
		Transaction tx;
		try {
			tx = sess.BeginTransaction();
			//do some work
			...
			tx.Commit();
		} catch (Exception e) {
			if (tx != null) tx.Rollback();
			throw;
		} finally {
			sess.Close();
		}

members.member:

The suffix identifies a particular column of results in the SQL IDataReader;
implemented by all subclasses

